The paper discusses count-based distributional semantic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). The focus on semantic composition and the use of grammatical types suggest that the paper is more likely to belong to the sub-category of CL (cs.CL) than other sub-categories. The use of inference and machine learning techniques also suggests that the paper could belong to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), or social and information networks (cs.SI).
